A quantum physics-inspired framework for accurate and interpretable uncertainty quantification in machine learning. By mapping kernel mean embeddings to a tensor network-based Hamiltonian and solving the Schrdinger equation, the model quantifies uncertainty for tasks like change point detection and time series clustering.
